#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_rsync/06_rsync_inotify.md:127
#, no-wrap
msgid "    We are operating in Rocky Linux 8 server, using SSH protocol for demonstration.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_rsync/06_rsync_inotify.md:129
msgid ""
"For the password-free authentication login of the SSH protocol, please refer "
"to [rsync password-free authentication login](05_rsync_authentication-"
"free_login.md), which is not described here. An example of the content of a "
"bash script is as follows. You can add different options after the command "
"according to your needs to meet your needs. For example, you can also add `--"
"delete` after the `rsync` command."
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (bash)
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_rsync/06_rsync_inotify.md:130
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"#!/bin/bash\n"
"a=\"/usr/local/inotify-tools/bin/inotifywait -mrq -e modify,move,create,delete /rsync/\"\n"
"b=\"/usr/bin/rsync -avz /rsync/* testfedora@192.168.100.5:/home/testfedora/\"\n"
"$a | while read directory event file\n"
"    do\n"
"        $b &>> /tmp/rsync.log\n"
"    done\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (bash)
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_rsync/06_rsync_inotify.md:140
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"[root@Rocky ~]# chmod +x rsync_inotify.sh\n"
"[root@Rocky ~]# bash /root/rsync_inotify.sh &\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_rsync/06_rsync_inotify.md:149
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    When using the SSH protocol for data synchronization transmission, if the SSH service port of the target machine is not 22, you can use a method similar to thisââ\n"
"    `b=\"/usr/bin/rsync -avz -e 'ssh -p [port-number]' /rsync/* testfedora@192.168.100.5:/home/testfedora/\"`\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_rsync/06_rsync_inotify.md:155
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    If you want to start this script at boot\n"
"    `[root@Rocky ~]# echo \"bash /root/rsync_inotify.sh &\" >> /etc/rc.local`\n"
"    `[root@Rocky ~]# chmod +x /etc/rc.local`\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_rsync/06_rsync_inotify.md:156
msgid ""
"If you are using the rsync protocol for synchronization, you need to "
"configure the rsync service of the target machine, please refer to [rsync "
"demo 02](03_rsync_demo02.md), [rsync configuration file](04_rsync_configure."
"md), [rsync free Secret authentication login](05_rsync_authentication-"
"free_login.md)"
